# 🪞 Reflections – Madavha Livhuwani

## 1. 💻 Reflection on Coding in Markdown (CV)

### Situation
As part of my digital portfolio assessment, I was required to code my CV using Markdown language. Before this task, I had little practical experience writing structured documents in Markdown and was more familiar with traditional word processors.

### Task
My task was to design and code a complete, professional CV in Markdown that clearly presented my education, technical skills, lab experience, and cybersecurity achievements in a readable and well-structured format.

### Action
I researched Markdown syntax and practised using headings, tables, inline code tags, bold text, and hyperlinks. I structured the CV with clear sections, used emoji icons to improve visual navigation, and formatted my technical skills as inline code badges for clarity. I also used a Markdown table to display my education history neatly and tested the rendered output to ensure it displayed correctly.

### Result
I successfully produced a clean, professional CV entirely in Markdown. The process improved my understanding of lightweight markup languages and showed me how developers use Markdown for documentation, README files, and portfolios. I now feel confident writing and structuring documents in Markdown for professional and technical purposes.

