## 3. 🌐 Reflection on the Use of GitHub Pages

### Situation
My portfolio needed to be publicly accessible online, not just stored locally. I was introduced to GitHub Pages as a free hosting platform, but I had not previously deployed a live website using it.

### Task
I was required to publish my digital portfolio to GitHub Pages so that it could be accessed via a public URL, and to reflect on the process of using version control and static site hosting in a professional context.

### Action
I created a GitHub repository for my portfolio project, committed my Markdown and HTML files, and configured GitHub Pages to serve the site from my repository. I learned how to structure the repository correctly, push changes using Git, and verify that the live site reflected my latest updates. I also linked the GitHub Pages URL and my GitHub profile throughout my portfolio documents.

### Result
My portfolio is now live and publicly accessible at [madavha-03.github.io/portfolio-/](https://madavha-03.github.io/portfolio-/). This experience gave me practical knowledge of Git workflows, version control, and static site deployment — skills that are directly relevant to modern IT and development environments. It also reinforced the importance of maintaining a professional online presence as a student entering the IT field.

